COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 852, L.D. 1277
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, removes anabolic
33 steroids from the definition of "controlled substance" in the laws governing controlled
44 substances prescription monitoring, rather than testosterone. The amendment also adds an
55 appropriations and allocations section.
